{"chunk_id": "625cbc4d-7209-4f0c-acbc-471a6e76d12a", "source_database": "ICMR", "document_title": "ICMR_NIN_Dietary_Guidelines_Real.pdf", "publication_version": "Latest", "chunk_sequence_number": 127, "content_type": "Medical Guideline", "language": "English", "text": "ILLNESS /c69Calcium is needed for growth and bone development. /c69Children require more calcium. /c69Calcium prevents osteoporosis (thinning of bones). /c69Milk, curds and nuts are rich sources of bio-available calcium (Ragi and GLV are also good dietary sources of calcium). /c69Regular exercise reduces calcium loss from bones. /c69Exposure to sunlight maintains vitamin D status which helps in calcium absorption. /c93Never starve the child. /c93Feed energy-rich cereals-pulse diet with milk and mashed vegetables. /c93Feed small quantities at frequent intervals. /c93Continue breast-feeding as long as possible. /c93Give plenty of fluids during illness. /c93Use oral rehydration solution to prevent and correct dehydration during diarrhea episodes. 37 Table 5 WHO New Growth Standards Standard", "embedding": [-0.08636575937271118, -0.018460014835000038, 0.020468952134251595, 0.04709923267364502, -0.04689544811844826, 0.0037396808620542288, -0.06092291325330734, 0.07630480825901031, -0.06749262660741806, -0.026090603321790695, -0.030924150720238686, -0.05101103335618973, -0.030658027157187462, 0.013018938712775707, -0.049184270203113556, -0.1004093736410141, 0.016513871029019356, 0.107038713991642, -0.0269243735820055, -0.07368959486484528, 0.00747997872531414, 0.011565085500478745, 0.04558916389942169, -0.003514951793476939, 0.014916489832103252, -0.0008982160943560302, 0.011625533923506737, 0.00325016095302999, 0.023467516526579857, 0.04010069742798805, 0.00741098215803504, 0.008506123907864094, 0.06811343133449554, -0.042866263538599014, -0.03975679352879524, 0.06061605364084244, 0.06875284761190414, -0.05300580710172653, -0.10272524505853653, -0.02112860046327114, 0.04501238837838173, 0.01108429953455925